com.authlete.cbor.tag

Interface CBORTagProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    COSEMessageTagProcessor, CPBignum, CPDefault, CPUntag, CPUri, CWTTagProcessor

    public interface CBORTagProcessor
    The interface for tag processors.

    Tag processors can be registered by CBORTagProcessor.setTagProcessor(Number, CBORTagProcessor).

    See Also:
    RFC 8949, 3.4. Tagging of Items

      CBORItem process(Number tagNumber, CBORItem tagContent)
      Process a tag.

    • Method Detail

      • process

        CBORItem process(Number tagNumber,
                 CBORItem tagContent)
          throws CBORDecoderException
        Process a tag.

        The CBOR data item returned by this method replaces the current tagged item (CBORTaggedItem).

        The simplest implementation is to return tagContent as is. It means that the tag is just removed. (cf. CPUntag)

        The second simplest implementation is to create a CBORTaggedItem instance with the tag number and the tag content passed as arguments and return it. (cf. CPDefault)

        Parameters:
        tagNumber - The tag number.
        tagContent - The tag content.
        Returns:
        A CBOR data item which replaces the current tagged item (CBORTaggedItem).
        Throws:
        CBORDecoderException
